","1293":"1293","1270":"1270","1349":"1349","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1314":"1314","Abt 1311":"about 1311","1323":"1323","1257":"1257","1311":"1311","1365":"1340","1453":"1453","1277":"1277","about 1304":"about 1304","1307":"1307","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Sheviock, Cornwall, England":"Sheviock, Cornwall, England","Stoke, Cheshire, England":"Stoke, Cheshire, England","England":"England","Adeston, , Devon, England":"Devon, England","Devon, England":"Devon, England","Of,, Devonshire, England":"Devon, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Clarice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Medieval English and French form of the Latin name <i>Claritia</i>. This may have meant ‘fame’ (an abstract derivative of <i>clārus</i> ‘famous’), but as a given name it may have been no more than an arbitrary elaboration of   Clara .  It was borne by a character who features in some versions of the medieval romances of Roland and the other paladins of Charlemagne, and in recent times by the ceramic artist  Clarice Cliff  (  1899–1972 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Claris","meanings":["Medieval English and French form of the Latin name <i>Claritia</i>. This may have meant ‘fame’ (an abstract derivative of <i>clārus</i> ‘famous’), but as a given name it may have been no more than an arbitrary elaboration of   Clara .  It was borne by a character who features in some versions of the medieval romances of Roland and the other paladins of Charlemagne, and in recent times by the ceramic artist  Clarice Cliff  (  1899–1972 )."]},{"name":"Clarisse","meanings":["Medieval English and French form of the Latin name <i>Claritia</i>. This may have meant ‘fame’ (an abstract derivative of <i>clārus</i> ‘famous’), but as a given name it may have been no more than an arbitrary elaboration of   Clara .  It was borne by a character who features in some versions of the medieval romances of Roland and the other pal